. In the 16th and 17th centuries, there was a good deal of interchange between <i>Edmund</i> and <i>Edward</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":12,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Edmund Bozum was born about 1370, in South Tawton, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert Bozum, was 17 and his mother, Jane St. George, was 16. He married Mabel Falewell. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1408, in South Tawton, Devon, England, at the age of 39."},"et":{"Abt 1370–1408":"umbes 1370–1408","1370–1408":"1370–1408","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1370–Female":"1370–Surnud","1390–1440":"1390–1440","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1355–1387":"1355–1387","about 1370":"umbes 1370","Abt 1370":"umbes 1370","1355":"1355","1387":"1387","1440":"1440","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","Dittisham, Devon, England":"Dittisham, Devon, England","South Tawton, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"South Tawton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","South Tawton, Devon, England":"South Tawton, Devon, England","Leigh Bretville, Plympton St Mary, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1370–1408":"noin 1370–1408","1370–1408":"1370–1408","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1370–Female":"1370–Kuollut","1390–1440":"1390–1440","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1355–1387":"1355–1387","about 1370":"noin 1370","Abt 1370":"noin 1370","1355":"1355","1387":"1387","1440":"1440","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","Dittisham, Devon, England":"Dittisham, Devon, England","South Taw